<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06040e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06040e">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06040e"> 40(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> jeu (recreated / debordement)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Suivant une opinion tr&egrave;s populaire et tr&egrave;s ancienne, le <mark>jeu</mark> serait essentiellement un d&eacute;lassement, une r&eacute;paration, une restitution de forces ou, come on dit, <mark>une r&eacute;cr&eacute;ation</mark>, c&apos;est-&agrave;-dire une cr&eacute;ation nouvelle &hellip;. &hellip; Cette explication du jeu par la r&eacute;cr&eacute;ation renferme une part de la v&eacute;rit&eacute;. &hellip; Une th&eacute;orie &hellip; explique le jeu par un exc&eacute;dent de force nerveuse, d&apos;&eacute;nergie vitale, par la d&eacute;pense d&apos;une activit&eacute; superflue. &hellip; Quand le lion n&apos;est pas tourment&eacute; par la faim et qu&apos;aucun animal ne le provoque au combat, sa force inoccup&eacute;e se cr&eacute;e &agrave; elle-m&ecirc;me un objet: il remplit le d&eacute;sert sonore de rugissements de d&eacute;fi, et sa force <mark>d&eacute;bordante</mark> se consume sans but. <font color="green">[According to a very popular and very old opinion, the game would be essentially a relaxation, a repair, a restitution of forces or, as we say, a recreation, that is to say a new creation .... ... This explanation of play by recreation contains some of the truth. ... A theory ... explains the game by an excess of nervous force, of vital energy, by the expense of superfluous activity. ... When the lion is not tormented by hunger and no animal provokes him in battle, his unoccupied strength creates an object for himself: he fills the desert with roars of defiance, and his boundless strength Consume without purpose.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 23</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
